2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 178
BY REPRESENTATIVE BOYER
A RESOLUTION
To commend Emma Renee Bonin on being named the 2026-2027 St. Francis Regis Church
30th Étouffée Festival Queen.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Emma Renee Bonin for her achievements
and to commend her on being named the 2026-2027 30th Étouffée Festival Queen; and
WHEREAS, Emma is a nineteen-year-old native of New Iberia, Louisiana, and a
2025 graduate of New Iberia Senior High School; and
WHEREAS, Emma is freshman at the University of Louisiana at Lafayette, where
she studies kinesiology, has a 3.8 GPA, and received President's List honors; and
WHEREAS, Emma is a member of the Kinesiology Professional Association, and
she participates in the Life on Purpose small group at Our Savior's Church; she works at
Tutu Cute Vinyl Creations and is a cheer coach at New Heights Gymnastics; and
WHEREAS, Emma is a survivor of a head-on collision caused by a drunk driver; she
dedicates her time advocating against impaired driving and educating teens and adults about
risks associated with drunk driving; and
WHEREAS, Emma volunteers at festivals across Louisiana, and in her free time, she
enjoys hunting, fishing, and watching college baseball; she plans to pursue a career as an
athletic trainer and hopes to work with special needs athletes competing in the Special
Olympics; and
WHEREAS, Emma Renee Bonin is an inspiring young woman who is most
deserving of the highest recognition for her academic achievements and advocacy and for
being named the 30th Étouffée Festival Queen.
